aviciModuleMIB.description: This MIB module specifies those managed objects that monitor and control a forwarding module.

aviciModuleTable.name: aviciModuleTable
aviciModuleTable.description: This table contains parameters and state variables for all modules in the system.

aviciModuleEntry.name: aviciModuleEntry

aviciModuleAdminStatus.name: aviciModuleAdminStatus
aviciModuleAdminStatus.description: The administrative state of this module.

aviciModuleOperStatus.name: aviciModuleOperStatus
aviciModuleOperStatus.description: The operating state of the module.

aviciModuleUpTime.name: aviciModuleUpTime
aviciModuleUpTime.description: The time in 100ths of seconds since the the module booted.

aviciModuleCurrTemp.name: aviciModuleCurrTemp
aviciModuleCurrTemp.description: The current temperature of the module in degrees C.

aviciModuleMaxTemp.name: aviciModuleMaxTemp
aviciModuleMaxTemp.description: The maximum temperature reported by the module in degrees C.

aviciModuleDescr.name: aviciModuleDescr
aviciModuleDescr.description: A text string containing a description of the type of module card in the slot.

aviciModuleAssySerialNumber.name: aviciModuleAssySerialNumber

aviciModuleLineSerialNumber.name: aviciModuleLineSerialNumber
aviciModuleLineSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the line card attached to the module in the slot.

aviciModuleMbSerialNumber.name: aviciModuleMbSerialNumber
aviciModuleMbSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the mother board in the slot.

aviciModuleAssyRevision.name: aviciModuleAssyRevision
aviciModuleAssyRevision.description: The revision number of the module assembly in the slot.

aviciModuleLineRevision.name: aviciModuleLineRevision
aviciModuleLineRevision.description: The revision number of the line card attached to the module in the slot.

aviciModuleMbRevision.name: aviciModuleMbRevision
aviciModuleMbRevision.description: The revision number of the mother board in the slot.

aviciModuleSoftwareVersion.name: aviciModuleSoftwareVersion
aviciModuleSoftwareVersion.description: The version of the software running on the module in the slot.

aviciModuleFirmwareVersion.name: aviciModuleFirmwareVersion
aviciModuleFirmwareVersion.description: The version of the firmware running on the module in the slot.

aviciModuleAssyProductId.name: aviciModuleAssyProductId
aviciModuleAssyProductId.description: The product identification number of the module assembly in the slot.

aviciModuleLinePartNumber.name: aviciModuleLinePartNumber
aviciModuleLinePartNumber.description: The part number of the line card attached to the module in the slot.

aviciModuleMbPartNumber.name: aviciModuleMbPartNumber
aviciModuleMbPartNumber.description: The part number of the mother board in the slot.

aviciModuleIpTable.name: aviciModuleIpTable
aviciModuleIpTable.description: This table contains the per-module Avici proprietary IP counters.

aviciModuleIpEntry.name: aviciModuleIpEntry
aviciModuleIpEntry.description: The per module aggregate IP counters.

aviciModuleIpInReceives.name: aviciModuleIpInReceives
aviciModuleIpInReceives.description: The total number of input datagrams received from interfaces, including those received in error.

aviciModuleIpInHdrErrors.name: aviciModuleIpInHdrErrors
aviciModuleIpInHdrErrors.description: The number of input datagrams discarded due to errors in their IP headers, including bad checksums, version number mismatch, other format errors, time-to-live exceeded, errors discovered in processing their IP options, etc.

aviciModuleIpInAddrErrors.name: aviciModuleIpInAddrErrors
aviciModuleIpInAddrErrors.description: The number of input datagrams discarded because the IP address in their IP header's destination field was not a valid address to be received at this entity. This count includes invalid addresses (e.g., 0.0.0.0) and addresses of unsupported Classes (e.g., Class E). For entities which are not IP routers and therefore do not forward datagrams, this counter includes datagrams discarded because the destination address was not a local address.

aviciModuleIpForwDatagrams.name: aviciModuleIpForwDatagrams
aviciModuleIpForwDatagrams.description: The number of input datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination, as a result of which an attempt was made to find a route to forward them to that final destination. In entities which do not act as IP routers, this counter will include only those packets which were Source-Routed via this entity, and the Source-Route option processing was successful.

aviciModuleIpInUnknownProtos.name: aviciModuleIpInUnknownProtos
aviciModuleIpInUnknownProtos.description: The number of locally-addressed datagrams received successfully but discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

aviciModuleIpInDiscards.name: aviciModuleIpInDiscards
aviciModuleIpInDiscards.description: The number of input IP datagrams for which no problems were encountered to prevent their continued processing, but which were discarded (e.g., for lack of buffer space). Note that this counter does not include any datagrams discarded while awaiting re-assembly.

aviciModuleIpInDelivers.name: aviciModuleIpInDelivers
aviciModuleIpInDelivers.description: The total number of input datagrams successfully delivered to IP user-protocols (including ICMP).

aviciModuleIpOutRequests.name: aviciModuleIpOutRequests
aviciModuleIpOutRequests.description: The total number of IP datagrams which local IP user- protocols (including ICMP) supplied to IP in requests for transmission. Note that this counter does not include any datagrams counted in ipForwDatagrams.

aviciModuleIpOutDiscards.name: aviciModuleIpOutDiscards
aviciModuleIpOutDiscards.description: The number of output IP datagrams for which no problem was encountered to prevent their transmission to their destination, but which were discarded (e.g., for lack of buffer space). Note that this counter would include datagrams counted in ipForwDatagrams if any such packets met this (discretionary) discard criterion.

aviciModuleIpOutNoRoutes.name: aviciModuleIpOutNoRoutes
aviciModuleIpOutNoRoutes.description: The number of IP datagrams discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Note that this counter includes any packets counted in ipForwDatagrams which meet this `no-route' criterion. Note that this includes any datagrams which a host cannot route because all of its default routers are down.

aviciModuleIpFragOKs.name: aviciModuleIpFragOKs
aviciModuleIpFragOKs.description: The number of IP datagrams that have been successfully fragmented at this entity.

aviciModuleIpFragFails.name: aviciModuleIpFragFails
aviciModuleIpFragFails.description: The number of IP datagrams that have been discarded because they needed to be fragmented at this entity but could not be, e.g., because their Don't Fragment flag was set.

aviciModuleIpFragCreates.name: aviciModuleIpFragCreates
aviciModuleIpFragCreates.description: The number of IP datagram fragments that have been generated as a result of fragmentation at this entity.

aviciModuleIcmpTable.name: aviciModuleIcmpTable
aviciModuleIcmpTable.description: This table contains the per-module Avici proprietary ICMP counters.

aviciModuleIcmpInMsgs.name: aviciModuleIcmpInMsgs
aviciModuleIcmpInMsgs.description: The total number of ICMP messages which the entity received. Note that this counter includes all those counted by aviciModuleIcmpInErrors.

aviciModuleIcmpInErrors.name: aviciModuleIcmpInErrors
aviciModuleIcmpInErrors.description: The number of ICMP messages which the entity received but determined as having ICMP-specific errors (bad ICMP checksums, bad length, etc.).

aviciModuleIcmpInDestUnreachs.name: aviciModuleIcmpInDestUnreachs
aviciModuleIcmpInDestUnreachs.description: The number of ICMP destination unreachable messages received.

aviciModuleIcmpInTimeExcds.name: aviciModuleIcmpInTimeExcds
aviciModuleIcmpInTimeExcds.description: The number of ICMP time exceeded messages received.

aviciModuleIcmpInParmProbs.name: aviciModuleIcmpInParmProbs
aviciModuleIcmpInParmProbs.description: The number of ICMP parameter problem messages received.

aviciModuleIcmpInSrcQuenchs.name: aviciModuleIcmpInSrcQuenchs
aviciModuleIcmpInSrcQuenchs.description: The number of ICMP source quench messages received.

aviciModuleIcmpInRedirects.name: aviciModuleIcmpInRedirects
aviciModuleIcmpInRedirects.description: The number of ICMP redirect messages received.

aviciModuleIcmpInEchos.name: aviciModuleIcmpInEchos
aviciModuleIcmpInEchos.description: The number of ICMP echo request messages received.

aviciModuleIcmpInEchoReps.name: aviciModuleIcmpInEchoReps
aviciModuleIcmpInEchoReps.description: The number of ICMP echo reply messages received.

aviciModuleIcmpInTimestamps.name: aviciModuleIcmpInTimestamps
aviciModuleIcmpInTimestamps.description: The number of ICMP timestamp request messages received.

aviciModuleIcmpInTimestampReps.name: aviciModuleIcmpInTimestampReps
aviciModuleIcmpInTimestampReps.description: The number of ICMP timestamp reply messages received.

aviciModuleIcmpInAddrMasks.name: aviciModuleIcmpInAddrMasks
aviciModuleIcmpInAddrMasks.description: The number of ICMP address mask request messages received.

aviciModuleIcmpInAddrMaskReps.name: aviciModuleIcmpInAddrMaskReps
aviciModuleIcmpInAddrMaskReps.description: The number of ICMP address mask reply messages received.

aviciModuleIcmpOutMsgs.name: aviciModuleIcmpOutMsgs
aviciModuleIcmpOutMsgs.description: The total number of ICMP messages which this entity attempted to send. Note that this counter includes all those counted by tsrIcmpOutErrors.

aviciModuleIcmpOutErrors.name: aviciModuleIcmpOutErrors
aviciModuleIcmpOutErrors.description: The number of ICMP messages which this entity did not send due to problems discovered within ICMP such as a lack of buffers. This value should not include errors discovered outside the ICMP layer such as the inability of IP to route the resultant datagram. In some implementations there may be no types of error which contribute to this counter's value.

aviciModuleIcmpOutDestUnreachs.name: aviciModuleIcmpOutDestUnreachs
aviciModuleIcmpOutDestUnreachs.description: The number of ICMP destination unreachable messages sent.

aviciModuleIcmpOutTimeExcds.name: aviciModuleIcmpOutTimeExcds
aviciModuleIcmpOutTimeExcds.description: The number of ICMP time exceeded messages sent.

aviciModuleIcmpOutParmProbs.name: aviciModuleIcmpOutParmProbs
aviciModuleIcmpOutParmProbs.description: The number of ICMP parameter problem messages sent.

aviciModuleIcmpOutSrcQuenchs.name: aviciModuleIcmpOutSrcQuenchs
aviciModuleIcmpOutSrcQuenchs.description: The number of ICMP source quench messages sent.

aviciModuleIcmpOutRedirects.name: aviciModuleIcmpOutRedirects
aviciModuleIcmpOutRedirects.description: The number of ICMP Redirect messages sent. For a host, this object will always be zero, since hosts do not send redirects.

aviciModuleIcmpOutEchos.name: aviciModuleIcmpOutEchos
aviciModuleIcmpOutEchos.description: The number of ICMP echo request messages sent.

aviciModuleIcmpOutEchoReps.name: aviciModuleIcmpOutEchoReps
aviciModuleIcmpOutEchoReps.description: The number of ICMP echo reply messages sent.

aviciModuleIcmpOutTimestamps.name: aviciModuleIcmpOutTimestamps
aviciModuleIcmpOutTimestamps.description: The number of ICMP timestamp request messages sent.

aviciModuleIcmpOutTimestampReps.name: aviciModuleIcmpOutTimestampReps
aviciModuleIcmpOutTimestampReps.description: The number of ICMP timestamp reply messages sent.

aviciModuleIcmpOutAddrMasks.name: aviciModuleIcmpOutAddrMasks
aviciModuleIcmpOutAddrMasks.description: The number of ICMP address mask request messages sent.

aviciModuleIcmpOutAddrMaskReps.name: aviciModuleIcmpOutAddrMaskReps
aviciModuleIcmpOutAddrMaskReps.description: The number of ICMP address mask reply messages sent.

aviciServerAccessModuleTable.name: aviciServerAccessModuleTable
aviciServerAccessModuleTable.description: This table contains parameters and state variables for all server access modules in the system.

aviciServerAccessModuleEntry.name: aviciServerAccessModuleEntry
aviciServerAccessModuleEntry.description: The status and parameter values for a server access module.

aviciServerAccessModuleType.name: aviciServerAccessModuleType
aviciServerAccessModuleType.description: The type of Server Access Module (either primary or secondary).

aviciServerAccessModuleLinkStatus.name: aviciServerAccessModuleLinkStatus
aviciServerAccessModuleLinkStatus.description: Current state of the link to this Server Access Module as seen from the server's point of view.

aviciServerAccessModuleNumTransitions.name: aviciServerAccessModuleNumTransitions
aviciServerAccessModuleNumTransitions.description: The number of times this Server Access Module has transitioned into the primary role.

aviciServerAccessModuleLastTransition.name: aviciServerAccessModuleLastTransition
aviciServerAccessModuleLastTransition.description: The last time this Server Access Module transitioned into the primary role.

aviciModuleColdStart.name: aviciModuleColdStart
aviciModuleColdStart.description: An aviciModuleColdStart trap indicates that the specified module has powered-up.

aviciModuleWarmStart.name: aviciModuleWarmStart
aviciModuleWarmStart.description: An aviciModuleWarmStart notification indicates that the specified module has restarted.

aviciModuleDown.name: aviciModuleDown
aviciModuleDown.description: The aviciModuleDown notification indicates that a server is no longer communicating with the specified module after having established communication.

aviciModuleTemperatureNormal.name: aviciModuleTemperatureNormal
aviciModuleTemperatureNormal.description: The moduleTemperatureNormal notification signifies that the specified module is now operating within the normal temperature range. The current temperature is reported in the aviciModuleCurrTemp object.

aviciModuleTemperatureMinor.name: aviciModuleTemperatureMinor
aviciModuleTemperatureMinor.description: The aviciModuleTemperatureMinor notification signifies that the specified module is reporting a temperature above the minor temperature threshold but below the major temperature threshold. The current module temperature is reported in the aviciModuleCurrTemp object. When the reported temperature drops below the minor threshold, the aviciModuleTemperatureNormal notification will be sent to clear this fault.

aviciModuleTemperatureMajor.name: aviciModuleTemperatureMajor
aviciModuleTemperatureMajor.description: The aviciModuleTemperatureMajor notification signifies that the specified module is reporting a temperature above the major temperature threshold but below the critical temperature threshold. The current module temperature is reported in the aviciModuleCurrTemp object. When the reported temperature drops below the major threshold, the aviciModuleTemperatureMinor notification will be sent to clear this fault.

aviciModuleTemperatureCritical.name: aviciModuleTemperatureCritical
aviciModuleTemperatureCritical.description: The aviciModuleTemperatureCritical notification signifies that the specified module is reporting a temperature above the critical temperature threshold. The current module temperature is reported in the aviciModuleCurrTemp object. When the reported temperature drops below the critical threshold, the aviciModuleTemperatureMajor notification will be sent to clear this fault.

aviciModuleMisconfigured.name: aviciModuleMisconfigured
aviciModuleMisconfigured.description: An aviciModuleMisconfigured trap indicates when the fabric version mismatch, or a module in a multimodule set is not in the proper slot.

aviciModuleIncompatibleSW.name: aviciModuleIncompatibleSW
aviciModuleIncompatibleSW.description: The aviciModuleIncompatibleSW notification signifies that the module is running a software image that is incompatible with the server image.

aviciServerAccessModuleDown.name: aviciServerAccessModuleDown
aviciServerAccessModuleDown.description: The aviciServerAccessModuleDown notification signifies that a server access module has gone down.

aviciServerAccessModuleUp.name: aviciServerAccessModuleUp
aviciServerAccessModuleUp.description: The aviciServerAccessModuleUp notification signifies that a server access module has come up.

aviciAllServerAccessModulesDown.name: aviciAllServerAccessModulesDown
aviciAllServerAccessModulesDown.description: The aviciAllServerAccessModulesDown notification signifies that all server access modules have gone down.

aviciAllServerAccessModulesDownClear.name: aviciAllServerAccessModulesDownClear
aviciAllServerAccessModulesDownClear.description: The aviciAllServerAccessModulesDownClear notification signifies that at least one server access module has come up.

aviciModuleMIBCompliance.name: aviciModuleMIBCompliance
aviciModuleMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the aviciModule.

aviciModuleIpCountersGroup.name: aviciModuleIpCountersGroup
aviciModuleIpCountersGroup.description: Internet Protocol Counter statistics for the module.

aviciModuleIcmpCountersGroup.name: aviciModuleIcmpCountersGroup
aviciModuleIcmpCountersGroup.description: Internet Control Message Protocol Counter statistics for the module.
